The objective here is to take any given number — 0, 50, 52.1, 65.746251394184, etc. — and convert it into a number with two digits after its decimal point, rounded if necessary: 0.00, 50.00, 52.10, 65.75. 

There is a single method built into any JavaScript number value that allows you to do both things easily and automatically. If you're not sure what it is, Google this!  